Aksa Enerji, Bank Asya, Dogan Yayin: Turkey Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-05-12T06:40:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/aksa-enerji-bank-asya-dogan-yayin-turkey-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active in
Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the last
close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  fell 1,616.65, or
2.4 percent, to 65,643.34 yesterday.  Aksa Enerji Uretim AS (AKSEN)  : The Turkish power
utility’s first-quarter net income rose to 9.62 million liras
($6 million) from 5.22 million liras in the same period of 2010,
it said in a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  after the
market closed yesterday. Aksa Enerji dropped 10 kurus, or 2.1
percent, to 4.65 liras.  Asya Katilim Bankasi AS (ASYAB)  : The Turkish bank that
operates under Islamic lending rules said net income declined to
48 million liras from 59.2 million liras in the first quarter of
last year, according to a filing with the bourse after the close
yesterday. Bank Asya, as the company is known, was expected to
earn 73.3 million liras, according to the average of four
estimates compiled by Bloomberg. Bank Asya fell 13 kurus, or 4.6
percent, to 2.68 liras.  Dogan Yayin Holding AS (DYHOL)  : Turkey’s biggest media
group cut a demand to pay back-taxes and fines to 18.5 million
liras from 89.9 million liras by applying to the government’s
restructuring program. Its unit Dogan TV Holding AS’s tax bill
was reduced to 275.8 million liras from 1.41 billion liras,
Dogan Yayin said in a statement to the bourse after the market
closed yesterday. The group may also restructure remaining back-
taxes and fines of 1.36 billion liras, it said. Dogan Yayin
dropped 9 kurus, or 5.4 percent, to 1.57 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
